{
  "stem": "24515.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Number one, you know, I have forgotten by now whether this was before-- shortly before or shortly afterwards.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I know that my father took over the presidency of this [INAUDIBLE] group.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And when I came home and congratulated him on it, he shh, shh, shh, shh.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Quiet. ?] He didn't want mummy to hear it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because mummy was very much against his still being prominent and you know, in position to do something.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I know now-- I don't know when I learned this-- that he was fired by the Nazi takeover chap from his position as director of the [INAUDIBLE] bank for not being on duty on the November the 10th, and the weeks after.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And my mother had a big job trying to persuade him not to try to sue the Nazi.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You know, my father was still in a position and able or wanting to-- to-- to fight these things.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I also know that my mother took it upon herself, and father then went along, to start emigration proceedings.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "She went to the American embassy, of course.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I have a document, if you like to see it, the letter that she has been-- you know, the family has been put on a waiting list and so on and so on.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We know today the waiting list would have been 10 years.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I forget how many.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We know that the United States did not accept one threatened Jew or other persecutee from Germany or Austria.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Not one, in the entire history.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Most people have heard about the Saint Louis.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I know somebody who was on it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] She went to-- to-- other places.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I have the passport of my mother and my father.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "If you like you can see it later on.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
